Text: Re Realtime NYMEX quotesthe attachment Enron North America Corp From Victor Guggenheim PM To Kam CT Darron C CT William CT David CT cc Subject Realtime NYMEX quotes As discussed in the brown bag classes today many people would like to be able to see the NYMEX prices updated in realtime Attached is a modified TDS file that will listen to the NYMEX price When you open the file an error message appears but the file does work Just go to the listen page and you can see each of the months Please forward this file to your group if you feel it will be useful to them If you have any questions just ask VIctor

Re TDS Physical PositionsI recieved the following message from Phillip in which you requested our physical book org codes and what Tagg book name it is associated with Below is a list for the central desk If you need any other info let me know TAGG BOOK ORG REGION CODE FTINTCENMID CENTMIDSTH FTINTCENMID CENTMIDNTH FTINTCENMKT CENTMKTMIC FTINTCENMKT CENTMKTCG FTINTRAGULF CENTRAGULF FTINTRAGULF CEGULFNGPL FTINTRAONT ONTARIO IMSITHE SITHE FTINTCNTTRAN CENTRLTRSP FTPEOPLES PEOPLES Phillip M Love PM To Victor CT cc Subject TDS Physical Positions Forwarded by Phillip M LoveHOUECT on PM Russ Severson PM To Jeffrey C CT Kam CT William CT David CT Phillip M CT Darron C CT cc George CT Subject TDS Physical Positions In order for the physical desks to roll out positions into TDS a mapping is required between the Org region code used in Portcalc for the physical calc and the related Tagg book code that is used for that region An example would be similar to Org Region Code Tagg Book Code CENTRAGULF FTINTRAGULF This is just an example and might not be a valid grouping TDS knows the Tagg books to pick up it just does not know which physical region codes that are related to it Can you provide for your desk all Org Region Codes used on your desk and what Tagg Book it would relate to If you could send me the list I will forward them to the TDS developers Any questions or concerns please call me Thanks Russ x

Sep NXAVCPST Philip The attached file contains settle prices for crude The NXAVC code price is in cell D which I have highlighted in yellow There is also historical data in the file where you can verify prior months If you have any other questions please ask

FW sales to Kaztex for productionOriginal Message From Fore Jeanne Sent Monday November AM To Guggenheim Victor Subject sales to Kaztex for production Importance High Victor We have three deals sales to Kaztex for Ocotber production that Kaztex says arent theirs Deals and Kaztex says they belong to Nicor and not Kaztex We contacted Nicor and they also said they did not buy this gas from us Can you please clarify who should be paying for this gas The total amount for all three deals is so I really need to find out who should be paying for this as soon as possible Thank you Jeanne Fore Gas Settlements x
